42 COUNTY RECORDS: VETERAN DISCHARGE PAPERS
43
44 SECTION 8. ORS 408.425 is amended to read:
45 408.425. (1) Each county clerk who receives a request to inspect veteran discharge papers that
[3]

B-Eng. HB 4132
1 are recorded under ORS 408.420 shall produce the recorded discharge papers for inspection if:
2 (a) The request for inspection is made in writing;
3 (b) The request sets forth the name, address and telephone number of the requester;
4 (c) The request sets forth the name and the date of birth or the last four digits of the Social
5 Security number of the veteran; and
6 (d) The request is made by:
7 (A) The veteran or [the spouse, legal guardian] a person holding a power of attorney for the
8 veteran or personal representative of the veteran;
9 (B) A county veterans’ service officer appointed under ORS 408.410;
10 (C) A representative of the Department of Veterans’ Affairs; or
11 (D) A licensed funeral establishment seeking to ascertain if a decedent was a veteran for the
12 purpose of obtaining veteran’s burial benefits.
13 (2) This section does not create a cause of action and may not be asserted as the basis of a per
14 se negligence claim.
15 (3) Each county clerk may adopt additional policies in order to protect recorded discharge pa-
16 pers from malicious or unlawful use and policies regarding copying of recorded discharge papers.
17 (4) Each county clerk shall maintain in the records of the county clerk a copy of each request
18 for inspection of recorded discharge information for a period of at least 10 years after the date the
19 request is received by the county clerk.
20 SECTION 9. ORS 192.390 is amended to read:
21 192.390. (1) Notwithstanding ORS 192.338, 192.345 and 192.355 and except as otherwise provided
22 in ORS 192.398, public records that are more than 25 years old shall be available for inspection.
23 (2) This section does not apply to records that are exempt from disclosure pursuant to
24 ORS 192.355 (37) or 408.425.
